In comparison to its European peers, France’s policy is among the strictest. By banning not only sales but also possession/use, France goes slightly further than even Belgium or the Netherlands (which ban sales but do not criminalize end-users as explicitly). France also lumped all oral nicotine products together (including novel forms like nicotine candies or gels) in one blanket ban, whereas some countries have taken a piecemeal approach. The French government did consider the experience of others: it cited the “discreet and invisible use” of pouches (a known issue from snus in Sweden) and the rapid uptake by youth (citing data like 12% of Danish young people use pouches) as justification for preemptive action
