The European public health community is watching France’s move closely. Some fear that if differing national rules persist (ban in one country, free sale next door), a black market and cross-border trade will flourish. Indeed, French officials acknowledge that cooperation is needed – for example, Belgium’s health ministry noted that France’s and the Netherlands’ bans would help reinforce their own, by reducing supply in neighboring regions
