. By contrast, the nicotine/tobacco industry is adjusting: some companies may withdraw pouch products from the French market and focus on other countries, while continuing to lobby for regulatory (re)consideration. Notably, British American Tobacco in late 2025 called for a more “coordinated EU approach” rather than piecemeal national bans, fearing a patchwork of laws and possibly hoping for a compromise solution at EU level
